<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Dr</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 13pt 35.45pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Rolls-Royce Group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (RaD0019)</span></p><h1 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt; orphans:0; page-break-after:avoid; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Declaration of Interest</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Rolls-Royce is a global business providing integrated power systems for use on land, at sea and in the air.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  We employ 42,800 people in more than 50 countries, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ith over half </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> employees </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">based in the UK.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In 2012 Rolls-Royce invested £919m in R&amp;D</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, approximately two-thirds of this in the UK.  The Company is widely and consistently recognised as a leading practitioner of truly collaborative industry-academic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">,</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Rolls-Royce primarily operates two highly successful models for academic collaboration: its world-wide network of University Technology Centres (UTCs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> – not to be confused with the recent generic term ‘university technical college’ or similar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">), and its partnerships in Advanced Manufacturing Research Centres (AxRCs).  These partnerships have consistently delivered advanced technologies that can be traced through to many of today’s world leading products.  The majority of the Company’s fundament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">al research is carried out through collaboration with these centres, making them </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">essential</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Rolls-Royce </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has significant relationships with other research centres around the world, including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ational research centres in Japan, Singapore, China, Germany</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the USA</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and elsewhere</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A consistent strategy of developing long-term relationships</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has provided Rolls-Royce with close contact with world-class academic institutions, provided stability for the researchers, and given the Company and the academic institutions access to a wealth of talent and creativity to help protect competitiveness into</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the future.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Successful, leading concentrations of research such as these provide the UK with an ideal platform </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to play</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">major role in international research projects, offering significant opportunities to exploit the results. A long-term, focused approa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ch to ensure stability has been essential.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt; orphans:0; page-break-after:avoid; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Summary</span></h1><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We welcome the opportunity to provide inputs for future inquiries into R&amp;D funding in the UK. Beyond overall levels of R&amp;D a more differentiated view of the effectiveness of R&amp;D funding is necessary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uide the public debate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">On the global level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, it is important to understand and increase </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the attractiveness of the UK for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">private sector </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">R&amp;D. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Public funding for research and support for pull-through of research output promotes private investment and growth,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and stimulates additional inward investment by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">domestic as well as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">foreign companies.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It is clear that many of the other world economies are protecting or increasing their investment in research for just such reasons.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Major international businesses have to date invested in UK research because it is recognised as amongst the best in the world. However, other countries are becoming increasingly competitive and UK industry now has more choice than ever before.  Many Gover</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nments, for example Singapore and Germany, are investing heavily to develop their research capability and provide attractive incentives for Companies to move their R&amp;D efforts.  It should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be noted that much of this investment is based on a long-term nation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">al ‘vision’ that stretches well beyond a ten-year horizon.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We welcome the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">steps taken by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">overnment on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">esearch and development funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to link </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">industry sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> strategy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academic collaboration</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to support for research and technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. This creates cohe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rence and also supports </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bridging</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the gap between research and bringing innovation to market</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> particular in growth industries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">announcement of the Aerospace Technology Institute (ATI) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is an example </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">overnment investment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> support</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a strategy for growth</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Government worked with industry in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Aerospace Growth Partnership (AGP) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">set out a national ‘vision’ and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">define the strategy for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">securing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">long-term success </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of the industry. Both sides entered into </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> multi-year commitment to co-invest</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which provides essential continuity, and to do so at research and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> technology </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">levels</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">will enable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aerospace </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">advanced manufacturing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and future products </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to remain </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">world leading</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In this context </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we recognise that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">through </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Technology Strategy Board (TSB) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">overnment has developed efficient mechanisms for supporting joint collaborative research with universities. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The scope of funding avai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lable through the TSB should be looked at in the context</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of pulling through </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">early stage research to validated technology.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> We believe that the funding available to the TSB is too low to deliver all the early opportunities created in the UK.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Further, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we believe that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">EPSRC remains an effective body for funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research at univ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ersities. While there is some merit in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recent calls for streamlining the research councils, we are concerned that this should not lead to over-rationalisation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> into a single research council. S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uch a step would hurt diversity of research amon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">various industri</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es and hinder the adaptation of the individual council to the major drivers in the different research arenas.</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At EU level, the access to significant European </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">funding remains important to UK businesses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the means of support by UK govern</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ment </span><span style="font-fam