tyle="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The regional agenda of funding collaborative </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">R&amp;D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> appears to have been lost with the disbanding of the regional development agencies (RDAs), making it much harder to get SMEs involved. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A strong basis for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">economic growth is rooted in a sound understanding of a locality’s economic advantage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and how R&amp;D funding affects it.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We look forward to more information on how the new LEPs will be able to support larger businesses in the UK. We remain sceptical that the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">granularity of the LEPs is too fine to be effective in coordinating university activity to support local needs. Most LEPs will contain only one (many none) first class, research intensive university. The granularity of the 39 LEPs means that aligning multi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ple agencies across multiple universities to address major technical challenges will be no small </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">task. It is essential that Government retain an oversight capability to avoid duplication of activity and missed opportunity.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">No matter how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">locality</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is defin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed; individual universities, industries, regions and even countries must target</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> those areas of technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or expertise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> where a leading position </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">exists, or where</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> emerging </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">technologies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the UK has the business infrastructure and skill-base to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">become</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">world leading</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> exist. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This implies focus on those institutions with a proven track record of excellence and delivering impact.  It also means that some difficult decisions must be taken to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> support some activities in the ‘locality’, however defined.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">looking at universities, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">acknowledge the difficulty of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> map</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ping</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> excellent research to most sectors of the Industrial Strategy, and maps based on academic classifications may not do </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">justice to centres that excel in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">applied research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in particular</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  Whilst </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we can offer no simple </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">solution</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, there is extensive knowledge </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in major industries </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of those with whom successful collaborations are underway– this is likely to be a good proxy for those centres that carry out </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">work having a tangible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">impact on business. I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> highly unlikely that successful </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">businesses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">engage long-term with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> organisation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s that fail to deliver results.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We would welcome </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">discussion on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> additional metrics that recognise successful university-business interaction, and link continued funding aimed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> at UK growth to those metrics.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e make it clear that we do not advocate that current, traditional measures of researc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> excellence be simply replaced, and t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">here is no question that the quality of research and training in the UK must remain internationally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> competitive.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">However, i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t should be recognised that the traditional outcomes of research are not the only measure of success, especially when considering exploitation for the benefit of the UK.  We have yet to see how the ‘Impact metric’ introduced for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the 2014 Research Excellence Framework (REF)</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> will affect the outcome.  In calling for Universities to help “write the plan” for investing ESI funds, there </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a risk that they will do so to support (only) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> traditional measures.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Finally, we should not o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">verlook the potential synergies between sectors.  It is quite likely that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for example</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Aerospace and Automotive will draw on similar skills and capabilities.  In examining heat maps and other indicators of expertise, where we see overlaps in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">capability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, opp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ortunities to more effectively channel R&amp;D funds may become apparent.</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> 2013</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Annual report of Rolls-Royce Group Holdings, </span><a href="http://www.rolls-royce.com/investors/financial_reporting/annual_report/index.jsp"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://ww</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">w</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">.rolls-royce.com/investors/financial_reporting/annual_report/index.jsp</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Ingenious Britain, a report by Sir James Dyson, March 2010</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 7.